President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Meredith M. Broadbent for the position of Member of the United States International Trade Commission. Broadbent is currently a senior advisor at the Center for Strategic and International Studies (CSIS) and holds the William M. Scholl Chair in International Business. She has previous experience as a Trade Advisor at the Global Business Dialogue, Assistant U.S. Trade Representative for Industry, Market Access, and Telecommunications, and senior professional staff member for the House Ways and Means Committee. Broadbent holds a B.A. in History from Middlebury College and an M.B.A. from the George Washington University School of Business and Public Management.